text:
Third Avenue, north from and including 17th Street. At 190 Third Avenue, adjoining the N.W. corner of 17th Street, is the German-American Athletic Club, or Scheffel Hall, known for its popular restaurant.

May 21, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
188 to 194 Third Ave. (left to right) at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of East 17th Street, showing No. 192 under demolition. The ornate building, No. 190 is occupied by the German-American Rathskeller. This was formerly Scheffel Hall and a part of William Allaire's Restaurant which included the structure under demolition and that adjoining. Partially seen on the extreme right is No. 196.

August 7, 1937.

George D. Chinn.

(2)
Another view.

August 7, 1937.

Gift of:
George D. Chinn.

text:
E. 17th Street, north side, west from Third Avenue, to and across Irving Place. The low ornate structure at the right (No. 143 East) is now occupied by a Greek Orthodox Church. It was formerly Scheffel Hall, a German restaurant, owned and operated by one, William Allaire. View No. 2 shows this detail and its adjoining structure No. 141.

June 1938
Views 1 and 2

George D. Chinn
